post_text:
Hello Pittsfield Parents and Guardians,

As the Pittsfield Public Schools has NOT yet announced any plan or model for the fall, we would ask all parents and guardians to please make sure to fill out our FALL SCHOOL REOPENING FORM, one form for each child as soon as possible. We are very grateful to the almost 3000 forms we have received so far, but need an additional 2200 responses to ensure that each family and taxpayer is being heard. The link to the form is on our district website at www.pittsfield.net. This form was also emailed and texted to all families with their current contact information on file.

In order to accommodate all parents and guardian schedules and childcare needs, the Superintendent and Deputy Superintendent will be offering a virtual meeting during the week of August 3-7 to provide all parents and guardians an update on our planning progress. Virtual meeting information will be sent later this week.

post_text:
Pittsfield Public Schools Kindergarten Registration

Children who will be 5 years old on or before September 1, 2020 may be registered to enter kindergarten in the Pittsfield Public Schools in the fall. Parents and guardians should go to www.pittsfield.net and choose 2020-21 Online Registration Now Open from the District Home Page.
The following documentation will be needed to complete registration: child’s birth certificate, a utility bill or a rental/lease agreement for proof of address, child’s immunization records and a copy of the last doctor’s physical exam, parent/guardian photo ID.
Questions may be directed to our registration office by emailing ppsregistration@pittsfield.net or by calling 413-499-9507 (leave a message, your call will be returned).

http://www.pittsfield.net/family___community/registration/online_registration

Quarter 3 grades will now close on Friday, April 24, 2020.

Missing Assignments

Students can make up any missing assignments that existed before the closure on March 13, 2020.

If something from before school closed was assigned and can’t be duplicated electronically or virtually, teachers may offer an alternative to that same assignment.

The work assigned before the school closure can be graded.

PPS will call, email, and text all families to notify when you may view the Q3 final grade in PowerSchool.
